title: Atlantic Records 40th Anniversary MSG NYC (5-CD)1988
description:
Atlantic Records 40th Anniversary MSG NYC (5-CD)1988 ak320

On May 14, 1988, the Atlantic Records label held its 40th Anniversary Celebration by staging a non-stop concert lasting almost 13 hours[1] at Madison Square Garden, New York. The event was dubbed "It's Only Rock And Roll".
Some who had split up re-formed especially to perform at the concert.
Led Zeppelin performed as the last act.
